If I want to create an ann account in my Linux host, I run two commands:

sudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash ann
sudo passwd ann

After I have the ann account created, I can install heroku into the ann account:

ssh ann@localhost
rm -rf heroku-client.tgz heroku-client
wget https://s3.amazonaws.com/assets.heroku.com/heroku-client/heroku-client.tgz
tar zxf heroku-client.tgz
echo 'export PATH=/home/ann/heroku-client/bin:${PATH}' >> ~/.bashrc
bash
heroku status
